      "extra": {
        "message": "Jinja2 Environment with autoescape disabled\n\nThe Jinja2 Environment is instantiated with default settings, which means `autoescape=False`. Any user-controlled data rendered through this environment will not be HTML-escaped, enabling Cross-Site Scripting if user input reaches template output.\n\nImpact: User-supplied data rendered through this environment is not HTML-escaped, enabling XSS attacks.\n\nFix: Initialize the Environment with autoescape enabled: `Environment(autoescape=True)` or use `select_autoescape()`.",
